snippet: Webb, a former president of Concacaf and a vice president of FIFA who was arrested in May, has agreed to extradition and is currently in the United States.
abstract: United States prosecutors extradite FIFA official Jeffrey Webb from Switzerland, making him first of 14 indicted in May to be sent to the US for trial; faces charges that he sought bribes in return for lucrative television deals regarding soccer games; prosecutors also reveal that they are in plea deal negotiations with sports marketing executive Aaron Davidson.

byline.original: By STEPHANIE CLIFFORD and WILLIAM K. RASHBAUM

lead_paragraph: Webb, a former president of Concacaf and a vice president of FIFA who was arrested in May, has agreed to extradition and is currently in the United States.

headline.main: Jeffrey Webb, Top FIFA Official, Said to Be in U.S. After Agreeing to Extradition
headline.print_headline: FIFA Executive Said to Be in U.S. After Agreeing to Extradition
